race.comment: ARUGAMAMA (2) looks the one and she might be ready to peak after four runs this campaign and getting out to this distance. Her last-start performance over 2000m was solid behind an in-form horse. She's drawn well and gets in nicely after the claim. TEST THE LAW (1) is a classy galloper that finished two lengths behind ARUGAMAMA last time. He might be looking for the extended trip now, although he has never won beyond 2250m. He will likely roll forward and make his own luck somewhere near the front. SALSITA (4) brings some different form lines, having raced very consistently in Victoria in recent weeks. He will get all the favours from a low draw with Crowther aboard. SMILING ASSASSIN (3) is always a top three chance in these staying races, while JACKSON RUN (5) might be ready to improve.
